    <thetext>Description of problem:
 The way the versionlock blacklisting of packages works is roughly:

  while line in file:
    pkgs = find_packages(line)
    exclude_packages(pkgs)

...one problem here is that excluding packages removes the cache that find_packages() uses, so every lookup takes ~0.1 of a second.
 If you put all the pkgs in a set() and exclude that once at the end it goes much faster.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
0.10.0

Steps to Reproduce:

dnf versionlock exclude nodejs\*
dnf list dnf</thetext>
